How to make a gene accummulation plot:


XXX. OrthoMCL groups.txt file into binary matrix for accummulation plot generation



XXX. GENE ACCUMULATION PLOT (RStudio)

Input the binary matrix file created from running groups_matrix.py on the OrthoMCL groups.txt file and the goodproteins.fasta file.
	$ python groups_matrix.py goodprotein.fasta groups.txt >out.matrix

Open R Studio and install the vegan package:
	> install.packages("vegan")
	> library(vegan)

Import your data:
	> rhodo.out <- read.table("~/Documents/vegan/rhodo-out.matrix", header=TRUE, quote="\"")

Run vegan:
	> sp <- specaccum(rhodo.out, method = "random", permutations=100)

View data (optional):
	> summary(sp)

Plot data:
	> plot(sp, ci.type= "poly", col="blue", lwd=2, ci.lty=0, ci.col="lightblue", xlab="Genomes", ylab="Proteins", main="Gene accumulation plot")

Add boxplot to data:
	> boxplot(sp, col="yellow", add=TRUE)
